        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:03PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>Showers and thunderstorms will increase over the next hour across
both the El Paso and Las Cruces metro areas.

At 4 PM, an outflow boundary was pushing north from Juarez and the
Lower Valley, and triggering scattered showers and thunderstorms
in its wake. Heavy rainfall has already started developing around
Horizon City and Socorro, and will likely spread into other parts
of El Paso as outflow encounters the Franklin Mountains.

In Las Cruces, weaker outflow is gradually pushing in from the
north, and has been triggering heavy showers and thunderstorms
around Magdalena Peak. These storms will spread into the Las
Cruces area in the next hour or so.

In both locations, brief heavy downpours will be the main threat,
with isolated spot flooding in poor drainage areas, especially
where storms may linger a little longer.

Otherwise, be aware of ponding on the road and the risk of
hydroplaning.
</description>
